Package: sfarrow
Title: Read/Write Simple Feature Objects ('sf') to Parquet Files with 'Apache Arrow'
Version: 0.4.0
Date: 2021-06-17
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Chris",
           family = "Jochem",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "w.c.jochem@soton.ac.uk",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-2192-5988"))
Description: An R implementation to read/write Simple Feature ('sf') spatial objects from/to Parquet files. Parquet files are an open-source, column-oriented data storage format from Apache (<https://parquet.apache.org/>), now popular across programming languages. This implementation converts simple feature list geometries into well-known binary format for use by 'arrow', and coordinate reference system information is maintained in standard metadata formats.
